.TH spop 1
.SH NAME
\*Lspop\*O \- POP mailer
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
.sS
\*L/usr/local/lib/mh/spop\*O
.sE
.SH DESCRIPTION
.iX "spop command"
.PP
The \*Lspop\*O
command delivers mail to the Post Office Protocol (POP) spool area on your
local system. POP is a service that allows you to
set up mail so that it is delivered on a larger system, rather than on a
smaller system.
.PP
Normally, you do not issue this command. Instead, the mail delivery
system uses this command as part of its normal processing.
.SH FILES
.PP
.VL 2i
.LI "\*L/usr/spool/pop/POP\*O"
POP database.
.LE
.SH RELATED INFORMATION
.PP
Commands: \*Lpopaka\*O(8), \*Lpopd\*O(8), \*Lpopwrd\*O(8).
